         <abstract>
            <p>A two-dimensional integral containing $\exp(-u - t)I_0(2\sqrt{ut})$ is considered. $I_0(z)$ is the modified Bessel function and the integral is taken over the rectangle $0 \leqslant u \leqslant x, 0 \leqslant t \leqslant y$. The integral is difficult to compute when $x$ and $y$ are large, especially when $x$ and $y$ are almost equal. Computer programs based on existing series expansions are inefficient in this case. A representation in terms of the error function (normal distribution function) is discussed, from which more efficient algorithms can be constructed.</p>
          </abstract>
